├── Adaptive Streaming
└── Content-Aware Coding

1. AI-Based Rate Control
Traditional codecs use:
Mathematical bitrate models

AI-based systems predict:
Motion complexity
Scene changes
Texture importance

Benefits:
Better bitrate allocation
Reduced buffering
Improved QoE

Used in:
Live streaming
Esports broadcasting
OTT delivery

Real-World Example
Netflix uses machine learning and perceptual optimization techniques for:
Content-aware encoding
Dynamic bitrate ladder generation
Better streaming efficiency

2. AI-Based Perceptual Encoding
AI identifies:
Visually important regions
Human attention areas

Then allocates:
More bitrate to important regions
Less bitrate to background

Examples:
Faces
Text
Gaming crosshairs
Players in esports

Applications
| Industry           | Example               |
| ------------------ | --------------------- |
| Esports            | ROI coding            |
| Video conferencing | Face prioritization   |
| Surveillance       | Person/vehicle focus  |
| Automotive         | Lane/pedestrian focus |

3. Super-Resolution Streaming
Instead of streaming full 4K:
Stream lower resolution
AI reconstructs higher quality
Example:
1080p Stream
      ↓
AI Super Resolution
      ↓
Near-4K Output

Benefits:
Lower bandwidth
Reduced CDN cost

Real-World Usage
Used by:
NVIDIA RTX Video Super Resolution
Samsung Electronics AI TV upscaling
Sony AI image enhancement

4. AI-Based Artifact Removal
AI removes:
Blocking artifacts
Ringing
Noise
Banding

This improves:
Low-bitrate video quality

Common in:
Streaming platforms
Smartphone cameras

Example
Modern TVs use AI enhancement after decoding compressed streams.

5. Neural In-Loop Filters
Traditional codecs use:
Deblocking filter
SAO
ALF

AI replaces these with:
CNN enhancement filters

Benefits:
Better reconstruction quality
Lower artifacts

Explored in:
VVC
AVS3
MPEG AI coding tools

6. AI-Based Motion Estimation
Traditional motion estimation:
Block matching
AI-based motion estimation:
Optical flow networks
Learned motion prediction

Benefits:
Better temporal prediction
Improved compression

Applications
Important in:
Cloud gaming
Fast-motion sports
Autonomous driving video

